            <title>[SPARK-34370] Supporting Avro schema evolution for partitioned Hive tables using &quot;avro.schema.url&quot;</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-34370</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This came up in &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/31133#issuecomment-773567152&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/31133#issuecomment-773567152&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;The use case is the following there is a partitioned Hive table with Avro data. The schema is specified via &quot;avro.schema.url&quot;.&lt;br/&gt;
With time the schema is evolved and the new schema is set for the table &quot;avro.schema.url&quot; when data is read from the old partition this new evolved schema must be used.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
